<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1429186" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/mopol.jpg?resize=600%2C338&#038;ssl=1" alt="Police deploy 5,000 personnel for Ondo LG election" width="600" height="338" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/mopol.jpg?w=1024&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/mopol.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/mopol.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/mopol.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/mopol.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/mopol.jpg?resize=200%2C113&amp;ssl=1 200w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Commissioner of Police, Ondo State Command, Bolaji Salami, says the command has deployed 5,000 cops to provide security on Saturday, for the Local Government Areas election. Salami said in a statement on Wednesday in Akure, that the command was fully prepared for the conduct of the election. He added that other security agencies including the Nigeria Security and Civil Defense Corps (NSCDC), and the Department of State Services (DSS) would collectively provide security during the exercise. Salami warned political thugs to eschew violence before, during, and after the polls and urged all participants in the election to adhere to the rules of the game. The commissioner revealed that the police had concluded arrangements to deploy more men to the state because of the October 10 governorship election. According to him, the men will be drawn from Edo, Osun, Ogun, and Ekiti states to ensure the peaceful conduct of the governorship election. Vanguard Mr Salami Bolaji, Ondo State Commissioner of Police, has warned that any politician with security aides or escort would not be allowed into the venues of the parties’ primaries holding this week. The police commissioner gave the warning in a statement issued by the command’s Police Public Relations Officer, ASP… July 19, 2020 In "Politics" Benue State Police Command, yesterday said it had mobilized and deployed no fewer than 5,000 police men to the Benue South zone, ahead of tomorrow ‘s senatorial rerun election between Senator David Mark of the Peoples Democratic Party and Daniel Onjeh, of the All Progressives Congress, APC. February 19, 2016 In "News" THE Acting Inspector General of Police, Ibrahim Idris, disclosed yesterday that a total of 23,000 policemen would be deployed to provide security for the September 10 governorship election in Edo state. August 26, 2016 In "News"